Social Media Marketing

  1. I can build an online audience that passionately engages with a brand or company
  2. I can drive and track revenue via social channels
  3. I can run paid social media advertising campaigns

Node.js

  3. I can speak about Node.js at meetups and conferences

Public Speaking

  1. I can deliver highly engaging presentations
  2. I can create visually compelling presentations to support my public speaking
  3. I can read an audience and understand the power dynamics of a room

CSS

  1. I can keep my CSS organized and well structured.
  2. I can overcome specificity problems that are commonly associated with the difficolty of quality CSS
  3. I can contribute to the open source community with CSS projects

Drawing

  1. I can compose a still life and create an accurate and realistic depiction of it with graphite and/or charcoal
  2. I can use and understand the roles of perspective in order to create more realistic drawings
  3. I can draw from memory and imagination

Customer Service

  1. I can show empathy to my clients concerns
  2. I can answer my clients questions in a timely manner
  3. I can provide creative solutions to address customer needs

User Experience Design

  1. I can assess user needs through research
  2. I can prototype conceptual designs to validate ideas
  3. I can design solutions based on identified user needs

data.value: How your application will be reviewed by others.

data.name: behaviorModal_Instructions1
data.value: Choose skill behaviors that show the depth and range of your skill level. Make your evidence detailed enough that a reviewer could understand your contribution level, your methodology, the challenges faced, and the outcomes achieved.

data.name: behaviorModal_Instructions2
data.value: When you are reviewed by peers, they will compare your application to another application in {{credName}} and determine which they believe “demonstrated more expertise.”

data.name: behaviorModal_Instructions3
data.value: When you are reviewed by the expertise panel, they will evaluate your application against a rubric that measures expertise based on characteristics such as autonomy, adaptability, and critical thinking.

data.name: behaviorModal_Instructions4
data.value: When you are reviewed by your endorsers, they will be asked to confirm that your skill behaviors and evidence are accurate and consistent with their experience working with you.

data.name: behaviorModal_Instructions5
data.value: Adding links or uploading files is a good way to demonstrate your skill but is not required. Make sure links are accessible and do not require a password to access.

  1. Visit Degreed.com and click Log In.
  2. Enter the personal email address you added to your Degreed profile and press Continue.
  3. If you have a password, enter it. If you don’t, don’t worry! Select “Forgot Password” to get a new one.
  4. Jump back in, right where you left off.

Since then, we've grown to over 3 million users worldwide who believe there is no single path to expertise.

data.name: UserPrivacyCtrl_ToOrgProfileFormat
data.value:
By changing your profile to 'Visible to my organization only', the following information will be available to {{OrgName}} users on this platform:

Your name, your learning collection ({{OrgNameSingular}} members), your insights (including leader board information).

Non-{{OrgNameSingular}} users will not be able to follow you (i.e. be informed of your learning activity).

data.name: UserPrivacyCtrl_ToOrgProfileFromAnonymousFormat
data.value:
By changing your profile to 'Visible to my organization only', the following information will be available to {{OrgName}} users on this platform:

Your name, your learning collection ({{OrgName}} members), your insights (including leader board information).

Non-{{OrgName}} users will not be able to follow you (i.e. be informed of your learning activity), and your information will be visible in organization's reports.
data.comment: Privacy disclaimer message for anonymous org user when changing to organization level privacy

data.name: UserPrivacyCtrl_ToPrivateProfile
data.value:
By changing your profile to private, the following information will no longer be visible to all users on this platform:

Your name, your learning collection, your insights (including leader board information).

Other users will no longer be able to follow you (i.e. be informed of your learning activity).

data.name: UserPrivacyCtrl_ToPrivateProfileInOrgFormat
data.value:
By changing your profile to private, the following information will no longer be visible to public or {{OrgName}} users on this platform:

Your name, your learning collection ({{OrgName}} content will not be visible to non-{{OrgNameSingular}} members), your insights (including leader board information).

Other users will no longer be able to follow you (i.e. be informed of your learning activity).

data.name: UserPrivacyCtrl_ToPrivateProfileInOrgFromAnonymousFormat
data.value:
By changing your profile to private, the following information will no longer be visible to public or {{OrgName}} users on this platform:

Your name, your learning collection ({{OrgName}} content will not be visible to non-{{OrgName}} members), your insights (including leader board information).

Other users will no longer be able to follow you (i.e. be informed of your learning activity), and your information will not be visible in organization's reports.
data.comment: Privacy disclaimer message for anonymous org user when changing to private privacy

data.name: UserPrivacyCtrl_ToPublicProfile
data.value:
By changing your profile to public, the following information will become visible to all users on this platform:

Your name, your learning collection, your insights (including leader board information).

Other users will also be able to follow you (i.e. be informed of your learning activity).

data.name: UserPrivacyCtrl_ToPublicProfileInOrgFormat
data.value:
By changing your profile to public, the following information will become visible to public (external to all {{OrgName}} users on this platform):

Your name, your learning collection ({{OrgName}} content will not be visible to non-{{orgNameSingular}} members), your insights (including leader board information).

Other public users will also be able to follow you (i.e. be informed of your learning activity).

data.name: UserPrivacyCtrl_ToPublicProfileInOrgFromAnonymousFormat
data.value:
By changing your profile to public, the following information will become visible to public (external to all {{OrgName}} users on this platform):

Your name, your learning collection ({{OrgName}} content will not be visible to non-{{OrgName}} members), your insights (including leader board information).

Other public users will also be able to follow you (i.e. be informed of your learning activity), and your information will be visible in organization's reports.
data.comment: Privacy disclaimer message for anonymous org user when changing to public privacy

data.name: WelcomeEmail_ConsumerParagraph1
data.value: What skills do you have? What skills do you want? How can you get those skills? Degreed is here to help you take on your future. We enable you to discover the skills you need to pursue your passions. You can set goals, build your skills, and track your progress.

data.value: Everything you see and do on Degreed focuses on skills you're developing. You are in the driver's seat. Take time to add relevant skills to your profile. Any skill you’re working on is fair game.

data.value: Accelerate your skill growth by learning from others. Follow other learners to learn together.

data.name: WelcomeEmail_ConsumerParagraph4
